&lt;h1&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Senior Physiotherapist&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h1&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Band 6&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;37.5 hours&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;9-12 months fixed term, Maternity cover&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Sandwell, Delta House&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;An exciting opportunity has arisen for a maternity cover Senior Physiotherapist – Band 6 to join our Adult Learning Disability Team in the Community. We are looking for a dynamic, enthusiastic and flexible Physiotherapist to work within the Sandwell Community team on a 9-12 month fixed term contract.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;As a Senior Physiotherapist, you will have responsibility for the provision of a high standard specialist physiotherapy service for adults with Learning Disabilities within the community.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You will work closely with other members of the mult-disciplinary team and therefore, the post holder will work in a team environment, having excellent communication and organisational skills.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You will be supported to continue professional development and will be an active member of the Trust physiotherapy team, receiving regular peer support. You will receive regular supervision and support.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The successful candidate will be required to undertake administrative tasks as well as providing direct clinical care in a rewarding environment.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further information about this exciting opportunity please contact:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Marie Heathcock - Principal Physiotherapist - m.heathcock@nhs.net&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Charlie Heaton – Service Manager for LD Community – charlie.heaton@nhs.net&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;NameMarie HeathcockJob titlePrincipal PhysiotherapistEmail addressm.heathcock@nhs.net&lt;/p&gt;
